Yaman Shuaib Abdullahi, the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, governorship candidate in Kwara State, has called on Governor Abdulrahman AbdulRazaq to conduct without delay, local governments election in the 16 councils of the state in compliance with the ruling of the apex court in the country. Yaman, also called on Kwarans in the nooks and crannies of Nigeria to go out and collect their Permanent Voter Cards, PVCs, which he described as the only document to guarantee a secured future and ensure that our democracy works for us. In his message on Sunday to commemorate the Democracy Day, in Ilorin, the PDP Governorship candidate said “Today is another wonderful day when we remember the labour of our heroes past, their sacrifices for us to live a life of freedom and equal opportunities, and strive even for a better future.” According to him “We remember their sacrifices, we should work in unison to fight corruption, lawlessness and executive rascality prevalent in our state of Harmony, Kwara State. “It is our collective responsibility to make the state better and the future of children secured.” Yaman, called on the “Kwara State Government to, without further delay and in compliance with the ruling of the apex court of the land, organise local government elections and stop further pilfering of our collective patrimony.” Yaman prayed God who determines the direction of everything, to direct wisdom, honour, mercy, good health and prosperity to Nigerians and their families.